Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on bandwidth estimation and congestion control for real-time communications, which are key topics in networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with optimizing user-perceived quality in real-time communications, which involves multimedia data such as audio and video. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper applies reinforcement learning, a subfield of AI, to the problem of real-time communications. 
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the challenges in designing realistic reward functions and bridging the gap between the training environment and real-world networks, which are relevant to software engineering. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with optimizing user-perceived quality in real-time communications, which involves information theory concepts such as bandwidth and data rate.
